17
00:00:52,381 --> 00:00:55,351
I was a huge fan of "Love and War."

18
00:00:55,351 --> 00:00:57,441
It feels like I've found an oasis.

19
00:00:57,441 --> 00:00:59,221
[I'm a viewer, Jang Do Yeon]

20
00:00:59,221 --> 00:01:02,461
Huh? What was that?

21
00:01:02,461 --> 00:01:04,501
That was a close one.

22
00:01:04,501 --> 00:01:06,321
[He gets sucked in so easily]

23
00:01:06,321 --> 00:01:08,041
[Empathetic angel, Cha Tae Hyun]

24
00:01:08,041 --> 00:01:10,211
My eyes weren't happy.

25
00:01:10,211 --> 00:01:11,471
It felt a bit showy.

26
00:01:11,471 --> 00:01:12,711
I'm not excited for the drama.

27
00:01:12,711 --> 00:01:14,381
I think it lacked a lot.

28
00:01:14,381 --> 00:01:16,191
[The harshest critic, Lee Byeong Heon]

29
00:01:16,191 --> 00:01:19,571
The vlog-style reel was quite long.

30
00:01:19,571 --> 00:01:22,001
It started with visuals with strong contrast.

31
00:01:22,001 --> 00:01:23,771
If I watched this on my own,

32
00:01:23,771 --> 00:01:25,771
I'm not sure if I could have followed the story.

33
00:01:25,771 --> 00:01:27,591
[The analytical prince, Jang Keun Suk]

34
00:01:27,591 --> 00:01:30,081
[Unpredictable results due to meticulous judging]

35
00:01:30,611 --> 00:01:32,531
[Then, this person showed up]

36
00:01:32,531 --> 00:01:35,091
[Receiving a warm welcome]

37
00:01:35,091 --> 00:01:38,021
I've been acting for 30 years now.

38
00:01:38,021 --> 00:01:39,551
I'm Choi Gwi Hwa.

39
00:01:39,551 --> 00:01:41,971
[Full of confidence]

40
00:01:41,971 --> 00:01:43,961
I know this will work.

41
00:01:43,961 --> 00:01:45,511
It will work with young audiences.

42
00:01:45,511 --> 00:01:49,041
I'm very excited to see it.

43
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:52,841
This year is my 30th year as an actor.

44
00:01:52,841 --> 00:01:57,041
I've worked in theater, film, and TV.

45
00:01:57,041 --> 00:02:00,931
As an actor, there's an aspect in life

46
00:02:00,931 --> 00:02:02,761
that hasn't been fulfilled.

47
00:02:02,761 --> 00:02:03,701
What's this?

48
00:02:03,701 --> 00:02:07,671
[He felt unfulfilled for the past 30 years]

49
00:02:07,671 --> 00:02:09,441
Move this in this direction a bit.

50
00:02:09,441 --> 00:02:14,601
[He's been filling the gap
by creating new stories]

51
00:02:15,821 --> 00:02:19,011
[But he still has his worries]

52
00:02:19,011 --> 00:02:23,551
My situation has improved,

53
00:02:23,551 --> 00:02:27,001
but I always need to ask someone for a favor.

54
00:02:27,001 --> 00:02:32,211
And I'm always in a place of hoping
someone else would choose me.

55
00:02:32,211 --> 00:02:38,921
I realized I've never been able
to do something on my own.

56
00:02:38,921 --> 00:02:43,701
I want to use this opportunity
to work in a position

57
00:02:43,701 --> 00:02:47,141
where I can reclaim and change my life.

58
00:02:47,141 --> 00:02:49,271
Please introduce your short drama.

59
00:02:49,271 --> 00:02:51,551
It's like a detective agency.

60
00:02:51,551 --> 00:02:55,651
He invites his clients to the restaurant
and finds a solution with them.

61
00:02:55,651 --> 00:02:59,431
A client commissions him with an adultery case.

62
00:02:59,431 --> 00:03:02,101
He brings the cheating man and woman in

63
00:03:02,101 --> 00:03:04,031
and finds evidence there.

64
00:03:04,031 --> 00:03:06,691
It's a loud, chaotic drama.

65
00:03:06,691 --> 00:03:08,761
Please play the video.

66
00:03:08,761 --> 00:03:11,281
I'm certain that it has the competitive edge.

67
00:03:11,281 --> 00:03:14,301
I know this will work.

68
00:03:14,301 --> 00:03:15,741
[Getting ready to watch]

69
00:03:15,741 --> 00:03:17,821
[Excited]

70
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:24,171
Secure evidence for adultery.

71
00:03:25,401 --> 00:03:28,521
I immediately went for it.

72
00:03:28,521 --> 00:03:32,231
[Choi Gwi Hwa's "Bistro, the Fixers"]

73
00:03:32,231 --> 00:03:34,091
I just need to do as I'm told, right?

74
00:03:34,091 --> 00:03:35,821
Everything can go to waste.

75
00:03:35,821 --> 00:03:37,721
[The lines are...]

76
00:03:37,721 --> 00:03:39,821
[not easy to decipher...]

77
00:03:40,431 --> 00:03:42,671
- Hey, Yun Jae Yeong!
- Where are you going?

78
00:03:42,671 --> 00:03:43,531
Where are you going?

79
00:03:43,531 --> 00:03:46,221
Have you been seeing each other for a long time?

80
00:03:46,221 --> 00:03:48,531
Just ask them if they're having an affair.

81
00:03:48,531 --> 00:03:50,331
Are you having an affair?

82
00:03:51,201 --> 00:03:52,951
For a long time.

83
00:03:52,951 --> 00:03:54,241
Hey.

84
00:03:54,241 --> 00:03:56,061
[The stop count is skyrocketing]

85
00:03:56,061 --> 00:03:59,001
- Come back quickly.
- It's going up too quickly.

86
00:03:59,001 --> 00:04:01,531
[Anxious]

87
00:04:02,601 --> 00:04:04,681
No, you can't get up.

88
00:04:04,681 --> 00:04:06,851
Stop the client!

89
00:04:15,481 --> 00:04:17,891
This is on the house!

90
00:04:21,811 --> 00:04:23,691
Is this Bollywood?

91
00:04:23,691 --> 00:04:25,691
[LOL]

92
00:04:25,691 --> 00:04:27,431
[Finally getting laughs]

93
00:04:27,431 --> 00:04:30,121
[The stop count stopped]

94
00:04:36,041 --> 00:04:37,561
We're fixers.

95
00:04:37,561 --> 00:04:39,041
No, we will be soon.

96
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:40,621
No, accidental killers.

97
00:04:40,621 --> 00:04:42,361
I'm a judge.

98
00:04:43,101 --> 00:04:45,191
There are no captions right now.

99
00:04:47,831 --> 00:04:49,621
Excuse me.

100
00:04:49,621 --> 00:04:52,541
Is this the place that helps solve
any kind of problem?

101
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:54,071
Because I really need some help.

102
00:04:54,071 --> 00:04:56,261
He hasn't paid much of it at all...

103
00:04:56,261 --> 00:04:57,791
Crazy bastard!

104
00:04:57,791 --> 00:04:59,671
Help me, please!

105
00:04:59,671 --> 00:05:01,181
Welcome.

106
00:05:01,181 --> 00:05:04,211
We'll fix any issues for you.

107
00:05:05,021 --> 00:05:09,561
[27, the stop count was higher than expected]

108
00:05:09,561 --> 00:05:12,321
I wish the latter part had come up earlier.

109
00:05:14,281 --> 00:05:16,531
What do you think of the result?
Are you satisfied?

110
00:05:16,531 --> 00:05:20,801
Yes, I'm just grateful that I survived.

111
00:05:20,801 --> 00:05:22,431
[I know how that feels]

112
00:05:22,431 --> 00:05:26,951
I thought about pressing the
button at the beginning.

113
00:05:26,951 --> 00:05:28,721
I wasn't really feeling it.

114
00:05:28,721 --> 00:05:32,051
I'm not sure why, but I wasn't feeling it.

115
00:05:32,051 --> 00:05:35,341
But when the music came on,

116
00:05:35,341 --> 00:05:38,761
it became kind of like a musical.

117
00:05:38,761 --> 00:05:42,151
That's when I started getting interested.

118
00:05:42,151 --> 00:05:44,161
Here's what I thought was most lacking.

119
00:05:44,161 --> 00:05:47,681
There are a few essential
elements in a short drama,

120
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:52,331
but I think one of them is captions.

121
00:05:52,331 --> 00:05:53,471
You need captions.

122
00:05:53,471 --> 00:05:55,071
I couldn't hear the lines well.

123
00:05:55,071 --> 00:05:57,691
We just became too used to them.

124
00:05:57,691 --> 00:06:01,391
The captions are expected in short-form dramas.

125
00:06:01,391 --> 00:06:04,331
They help you understand and
engage you more quickly.

126
00:06:04,331 --> 00:06:07,811
It was a shame that part was missing.

127
00:06:07,811 --> 00:06:10,111
Got it. Thank you, Director Choi Gwi Hwa.

128
00:06:10,111 --> 00:06:12,591
- Please go back to your seat.
- Thank you very much.

129
00:06:12,591 --> 00:06:13,941
[Director Choi Gwi Hwa's critiques
were disappointing]

130
00:06:13,941 --> 00:06:16,171
This is kind of a scary thing.

131
00:06:16,171 --> 00:06:20,921
When we were young,
we didn't always get captions.

132
00:06:20,921 --> 00:06:24,991
But it feels awkward when
they're suddenly not there.

133
00:06:24,991 --> 00:06:28,231
Right. It bothers you when
you didn't catch a word.

134
00:06:28,231 --> 00:06:32,091
- That's how much we got used to them.
- We really did.

135
00:06:32,091 --> 00:06:33,501
Good work, Hyungnim.

136
00:06:33,501 --> 00:06:35,921
It bothers you when you didn't catch a word.

137
00:06:35,921 --> 00:06:38,921
[He can finally relax]

138
00:06:38,921 --> 00:06:42,271
You did a good job, Hyungnim.

139
00:06:42,271 --> 00:06:43,831
[Feeling down...]

140
00:06:43,831 --> 00:06:47,211
[Choi Gwi Hwa gets a chance
to survive with 27 stops]

141
00:06:47,211 --> 00:06:49,461
[At night, at a film set]

142
00:06:49,461 --> 00:06:51,241
[Scream]

143
00:06:52,921 --> 00:06:55,161
[Bloody, creepy scene]

144
00:06:56,581 --> 00:06:59,461
[Keep hearing loud screams]

145
00:07:03,451 --> 00:07:06,551
[The heart rate is at 126 bpm]

146
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:09,041
[Who's the director of this
suspenseful short drama?]

147
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:11,231
[A delicate female director shows up]

148
00:07:11,231 --> 00:07:16,231
- Hello.
- You look very familiar.

149
00:07:16,231 --> 00:07:18,831
We know you as the actress Ahn Mi Na.

150
00:07:18,831 --> 00:07:23,591
Hello, I've been acting for about 20 years.

151
00:07:23,591 --> 00:07:29,231
You might know me as Ms. Kim in "Radio Star."

152
00:07:29,231 --> 00:07:33,161
- Oh, you're right.
- That was me.

153
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:36,391
- You were in "Steel Rain," too.
- That's right.

154
00:07:36,391 --> 00:07:40,351
[She's been in films and TV dramas
since her 2005 debut]

155
00:07:40,351 --> 00:07:42,751
[Ms. Kim never fails to make me cry...]

156
00:07:42,751 --> 00:07:45,011
I've been working as an actress,

157
00:07:45,011 --> 00:07:49,731
but now, I'm focusing on writing and directing.

158
00:07:49,731 --> 00:07:52,861
My name as a director is Jisam.

159
00:07:52,861 --> 00:07:54,211
[Actress Ahn Mi Na]

160
00:07:54,211 --> 00:07:55,611
[Director Jisam]

161
00:07:55,611 --> 00:07:57,851
[Debuted with an occult short film]

162
00:07:57,851 --> 00:08:01,361
[Occult: A study of supernatural, magical,
evil, mystical, and superstitious phenomena]

163
00:08:01,361 --> 00:08:04,261
[She's an active member of an occult club, too]

164
00:08:04,261 --> 00:08:06,991
[What kind of short drama did
Director Jisam make?]

165
00:08:06,991 --> 00:08:09,431
[Director Jisam's film set]

166
00:08:09,431 --> 00:08:12,021
He plays the lead, Jae Gil.

167
00:08:12,021 --> 00:08:13,791
I'm Hyun Woo Seok.

168
00:08:14,571 --> 00:08:17,201
[Installing a camera on the actor?]

169
00:08:17,201 --> 00:08:19,991
[A rare setup for a short drama]

170
00:08:19,991 --> 00:08:21,421
Action.

171
00:08:21,421 --> 00:08:23,101
[Body-mount shot]

172
00:08:23,101 --> 00:08:24,321
Cut.

173
00:08:25,551 --> 00:08:27,531
I like the feel of this.

174
00:08:27,531 --> 00:08:28,871
[Totally satisfied]

175
00:08:28,871 --> 00:08:32,321
[Sensitive directing from various perspectives]

176
00:08:32,321 --> 00:08:34,971
We're done with the scene. Let's move on.

177
00:08:34,971 --> 00:08:37,481
[Finally, the night shoot]

178
00:08:39,071 --> 00:08:41,491
[Setting up the exorcism scene]

179
00:08:41,491 --> 00:08:43,131
[The detailed makeup adds
to the scary atmosphere]

180
00:08:43,131 --> 00:08:44,281
[Gu Yeong played by Im Dong Yun]

181
00:08:44,281 --> 00:08:47,171
The character named Gu Yeong

182
00:08:47,171 --> 00:08:49,891
