204
00:09:57,691 --> 00:10:03,691
Right now, I'm only focusing on occult.

205
00:10:03,691 --> 00:10:10,091
You'll see more in-depth occult
than you expected.

206
00:10:10,091 --> 00:10:11,891
[The Archangel's Visit]

207
00:10:11,891 --> 00:10:15,591
[Ahn Mi Na's "The Archangel's Visit"]

208
00:10:17,311 --> 00:10:22,161
I give you the eyes of Gideon, the soldier.

209
00:10:23,551 --> 00:10:26,501
I-I think you're at the wrong place.

210
00:10:30,021 --> 00:10:32,141
- What?
- Gosh. Man Seok.

211
00:10:32,141 --> 00:10:33,231
[Daebak]

212
00:10:34,071 --> 00:10:37,871
[The archangel is actor Oh Man Seok]

213
00:10:37,871 --> 00:10:39,361
[The one who is gifted with eyes shall see]

214
00:10:41,461 --> 00:10:43,851
Snake!

215
00:10:48,331 --> 00:10:50,591
[Voting starts]

216
00:10:52,781 --> 00:10:56,281
[Will this occult short succeed?]

217
00:10:56,281 --> 00:10:57,751
You need to cover your eyes.

218
00:10:57,751 --> 00:10:59,921
They're looking for you.

219
00:11:04,251 --> 00:11:06,061
Get lost.

220
00:11:06,871 --> 00:11:08,731
[And he will flee from you]

221
00:11:08,731 --> 00:11:10,971
Though you soar like the eagle

222
00:11:10,971 --> 00:11:13,011
and make your nest among the stars,

223
00:11:13,011 --> 00:11:16,511
I will bring you down!

224
00:11:16,511 --> 00:11:18,631
This is the key to the abyss.

225
00:11:18,631 --> 00:11:21,051
When the gate opens after a thousand years,

226
00:11:21,051 --> 00:11:22,321
our king will come!

227
00:11:22,321 --> 00:11:23,921
[Scary]

228
00:11:23,921 --> 00:11:27,151
[Various reactions]

229
00:11:27,151 --> 00:11:30,481
The evil one cannot harm him!

230
00:11:33,541 --> 00:11:36,731
[The Archangel's Visit]

231
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:42,551
You should've come sooner.

232
00:11:42,551 --> 00:11:44,821
[You can watch the full versions on Lehzin Snack]

233
00:11:44,821 --> 00:11:47,001
[Judging ends]

234
00:11:48,671 --> 00:11:49,831
She worked hard on it.

235
00:11:49,831 --> 00:11:52,531
With 23 stops, Director Ahn Mi Na

236
00:11:52,531 --> 00:11:55,551
gets a chance to survive. Congratulations.

237
00:11:55,551 --> 00:11:57,251
Thank you.

238
00:11:58,201 --> 00:12:00,971
We saw a familiar face in the teaser.
It was Oh Man Seok.

239
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:02,531
Yes, it was him.

240
00:12:02,531 --> 00:12:07,071
I got a lot of help from my actor colleagues.

241
00:12:07,071 --> 00:12:09,091
I loved the beginning.

242
00:12:09,091 --> 00:12:10,741
It was very refreshing.

243
00:12:10,741 --> 00:12:14,381
The occult genre works in a short form.

244
00:12:14,381 --> 00:12:18,831
But it became a bit slow
somewhere halfway through,

245
00:12:18,831 --> 00:12:21,441
but it still got me curious.

246
00:12:21,441 --> 00:12:26,751
When the archangel appeared in the beginning,

247
00:12:26,751 --> 00:12:28,441
I wondered if it was comedy.

248
00:12:28,441 --> 00:12:30,971
I thought it was an occult genre at first.

249
00:12:30,971 --> 00:12:32,891
It was a bit confusing at first.

250
00:12:32,891 --> 00:12:35,451
It took me a moment to focus.

251
00:12:35,451 --> 00:12:37,071
[Disappointed]

252
00:12:37,071 --> 00:12:39,421
[Ahn Mi Na gets a chance
to survive with 19 stops]

253
00:12:39,421 --> 00:12:42,111
"Can't Live Without Dopamine Spikes."

254
00:12:42,111 --> 00:12:44,651
- That's powerful.
- Let's welcome the director.

255
00:12:44,651 --> 00:12:46,271
Nice to meet you, Director.

256
00:12:46,271 --> 00:12:49,551
I've made long-form dramas before,

257
00:12:49,551 --> 00:12:51,881
but now, I want to pivot to short-form dramas.

258
00:12:51,881 --> 00:12:54,011
I'm Director Go Hyeon Guk.

259
00:12:54,011 --> 00:12:57,441
You worked for eight years and four
months as a producer for SBS.

260
00:12:57,441 --> 00:12:59,751
You co-directed the mini-series "Big Issue."

261
00:12:59,751 --> 00:13:02,721
"Doctors," "My Mother Is a Daughter-in-law,"
"Band of Sisters."

262
00:13:02,721 --> 00:13:04,961
You co-directed many more.

263
00:13:04,961 --> 00:13:06,161
Gosh.

264
00:13:06,161 --> 00:13:08,961
Why is he here?

265
00:13:08,961 --> 00:13:13,421
You joined SBS through the public recruitment?

266
00:13:13,421 --> 00:13:15,721
- Yes.
- Why did you quit?

267
00:13:15,721 --> 00:13:19,621
Well, it's a long story.

268
00:13:19,621 --> 00:13:22,801
I don't look like it, but I tend to

269
00:13:22,801 --> 00:13:25,691
fight when I feel something's wrong.

270
00:13:25,691 --> 00:13:29,651
I'm no longer able to make dramas.

271
00:13:29,651 --> 00:13:31,991
I ended up in a difficult position.

272
00:13:31,991 --> 00:13:37,711
I thought I'd just end up as an office worker.

273
00:13:37,711 --> 00:13:40,001
So, I quit. To be honest, I'm regretting it a bit.

274
00:13:40,001 --> 00:13:41,451
[Totally regretting]

275
00:13:41,451 --> 00:13:45,521
It gets cold and hungry outside.

276
00:13:45,521 --> 00:13:47,911
[I'm thirsty]

277
00:13:48,631 --> 00:13:51,801
It'd be nice if you gave me a call.

278
00:13:51,801 --> 00:13:54,351
I learned my lesson now.

279
00:13:55,101 --> 00:13:58,701
To be able to direct again,

280
00:13:58,701 --> 00:14:01,241
instead of relying on someone else,

281
00:14:01,241 --> 00:14:05,211
I thought I should create something myself.

282
00:14:05,211 --> 00:14:06,911
That's why I applied.

283
00:14:06,911 --> 00:14:08,511
By the way,

284
00:14:08,511 --> 00:14:12,761
you were a finalist for the 2008 MBC
University Song Festival.

285
00:14:12,761 --> 00:14:14,031
What's this now?

286
00:14:14,031 --> 00:14:16,461
You were a rapper, on top of that.

287
00:14:16,461 --> 00:14:18,301
[Cheer]

288
00:14:18,301 --> 00:14:20,301
Everyone had a fun life.

289
00:14:20,301 --> 00:14:23,851
Could you rap briefly to express
your feelings now?

290
00:14:23,851 --> 00:14:25,491
I'm not great, but I'll try.

291
00:14:25,491 --> 00:14:27,381
[Wow]

292
00:14:27,381 --> 00:14:29,381
Thank you.

293
00:14:29,381 --> 00:14:31,111
[Here comes Hyeon Guk]

294
00:14:31,111 --> 00:14:32,661
Yo.

295
00:14:32,661 --> 00:14:34,701
A former SBS drama producer.

296
00:14:34,701 --> 00:14:38,461
Removed the title. I'm here again as a beginner.

297
00:14:39,871 --> 00:14:43,121
I want to paint on a new canvas
called "short-form."

298
00:14:43,121 --> 00:14:46,371
I hope I spike dopamine in everyone's brain.

299
00:14:46,371 --> 00:14:48,801
[The piercing lyrics]

300
00:14:48,801 --> 00:14:50,251
[Swag]

301
00:14:50,251 --> 00:14:52,281
He killed it. He killed it.

302
00:14:52,281 --> 00:14:54,301
Wow, Director...

303
00:14:54,301 --> 00:14:57,761
I'm even more curious about your teaser.

304
00:14:57,761 --> 00:15:00,511
"Can't Live Without Dopamine Spikes."

305
00:15:00,511 --> 00:15:04,161
The female lead is an unsuccessful drama writer.

306
00:15:04,161 --> 00:15:07,671
One day, she ends up in her drama.

307
00:15:07,671 --> 00:15:09,741
To maintain the world she's in,

308
00:15:09,741 --> 00:15:11,631
she has to collect "dopamine points."

309
00:15:11,631 --> 00:15:15,661
It's about her struggles
to collect dopamine points.

310
00:15:15,661 --> 00:15:18,621
Let's watch Director Go Hyeon Guk's teaser.

311
00:15:18,621 --> 00:15:20,591
Play the video.

312
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:26,621
I was worried as to how
my teaser would be received.

313
00:15:26,621 --> 00:15:29,551
[Can't Live Without Dopamine Spikes]

314
00:15:30,241 --> 00:15:33,011
I need dopamine spikes to live?

315
00:15:33,011 --> 00:15:34,431
- Yes.
- What if it doesn't?

316
00:15:34,431 --> 00:15:35,871
- You die.
- I die?

317
00:15:35,871 --> 00:15:37,371
You die.

318
00:15:37,371 --> 00:15:39,921
The drama writer who writes calm,
healing dramas

319
00:15:39,921 --> 00:15:41,481
became an extra in her work,

320
00:15:41,481 --> 00:15:43,571
but she's about to die because the story sucks?

321
00:15:43,571 --> 00:15:44,681
- Yes.
- Why?

322
00:15:44,681 --> 00:15:46,201
- That's just the setup.
- Unbelievable.

323
00:15:46,201 --> 00:15:48,861
That's how all dramas are.

324
00:15:48,861 --> 00:15:50,071
- Spare me.
- Pardon?

325
00:15:50,071 --> 00:15:52,551
I really want to live.

326
00:15:52,551 --> 00:15:55,971
The script you wrote is severely
lacking in dopamine points.

327
00:15:55,971 --> 00:15:57,111
Dopamine points?

328
00:15:57,111 --> 00:16:00,051
The points go up and down
depending on how fun it is.

329
00:16:00,051 --> 00:16:03,021
- Are you saying my script is not fun?
- Yes.

330
00:16:03,021 --> 00:16:04,611
It totally sucks.

331
00:16:04,611 --> 00:16:06,611
- Are you saying my script is not fun?
- Yes.

332
00:16:06,611 --> 00:16:09,381
- It totally sucks.
- You're crossing the line.

333
00:16:09,381 --> 00:16:12,381
It's all about dopamine-spiking
short dramas these days.

334
00:16:12,381 --> 00:16:14,871
Hold on. What's this number right now?

335
00:16:14,871 --> 00:16:16,801
- The points I mentioned.
- It keeps dropping.

336
00:16:16,801 --> 00:16:18,461
You die when it hits zero.

337
00:16:18,461 --> 00:16:20,321
- Right now?
- You'll die right now.

338
00:16:20,321 --> 00:16:22,121
[His expression is mysterious, too]

339
00:16:22,121 --> 00:16:23,811
Are you telling me to die right now?

340
00:16:23,811 --> 00:16:25,561
- I didn't say that.
- Excuse me!

341
00:16:25,561 --> 00:16:27,161
Pardon?

342
00:16:27,161 --> 00:16:30,221
<i>♫ Is anyone out there? ♫</i>

343
00:16:30,221 --> 00:16:32,531
[Hehe]

344
00:16:32,531 --> 00:16:35,131
[No reaction to people's laughs]

345
00:16:35,131 --> 00:16:37,411
What am I supposed to do?

346
00:16:37,411 --> 00:16:39,771
It's easy if you give up.

347
00:16:44,811 --> 00:16:46,231
What?

348
00:16:46,231 --> 00:16:48,491
[Coming on strong!]

349
00:16:48,491 --> 00:16:51,191
[My goodness!]

350
00:16:52,421 --> 00:16:54,121
Okay, the dopamine spiked.

351
00:16:54,121 --> 00:16:56,621
[Still expressionless]

352
00:16:58,301 --> 00:17:02,051
I'll give you 1,000 points.

353
00:17:02,051 --> 00:17:03,921
Whoa, shit.

354
00:17:03,921 --> 00:17:06,121
What a freaking dopamine spike.

355
00:17:06,121 --> 00:17:08,561
[Can't Live Without Dopamine Spikes]

356
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:10,901
[Cheering for the ending]

357
00:17:10,901 --> 00:17:13,161
[Mysterious blank expression]

358
00:17:13,601 --> 00:17:16,821
[Did the 90-second teaser spike dopamine?]

359
00:17:16,821 --> 00:17:20,321
Director Go Hyeon Guk, with...

360
00:17:21,431 --> 00:17:23,021
[Really?]

361
00:17:23,021 --> 00:17:26,741
With an 18-stop count,
you get a chance to survive.

362
00:17:26,741 --> 00:17:28,381
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

363
00:17:28,381 --> 00:17:30,011
[Congrats]

364
00:17:30,011 --> 00:17:32,641
He has tons of experience.

365
00:17:32,641 --> 00:17:35,771
He also made dramas for SBS.

366
00:17:35,771 --> 00:17:40,601
That means he's very
detail-oriented as a director.

367
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:43,691
I found it very eye-catching.

368
00:17:43,691 --> 00:17:45,831
That's what spiked my dopamine.

369
00:17:45,831 --> 00:17:48,171
[He successfully spiked everyone's dopamine]

370
00:17:48,171 --> 00:17:51,501
I realized people aren't that different.

371
00:17:51,501 --> 00:17:55,881
The number was going up,
but it stopped at the kiss.

372
00:17:55,881 --> 00:17:59,061
[The kiss scene stopped the stop count]

373
00:17:59,711 --> 00:18:03,091
[Everyone paused at that moment]

374
00:18:03,091 --> 00:18:05,841
And after the kiss, the count went up by two.

375
00:18:05,841 --> 00:18:07,981
[Agree]

376
00:18:07,981 --> 00:18:09,191
Kisses are important.

377
00:18:09,191 --> 00:18:12,261
You're right. You need a kiss scene in Episode 1.

378
00:18:12,261 --> 00:18:15,171
He knows how to draw people in.

379
00:18:15,171 --> 00:18:17,151
I could tell you're confident.

380
00:18:17,151 --> 00:18:18,731
I sensed your determination, too.

381
00:18:18,731 --> 00:18:21,891
I wondered if the whole teaser
would be their banter.

382
00:18:21,891 --> 00:18:23,521
That's what I expected.

383
00:18:23,521 --> 00:18:27,751
But the rhythm and pacing
showed your confidence.

384
00:18:27,751 --> 00:18:29,491
It was actually fun.

385
00:18:29,491 --> 00:18:32,501
It was worth not pushing the button in the end.

386
00:18:32,501 --> 00:18:34,181
Thank you.

387
00:18:34,181 --> 00:18:35,911
You get a chance to survive.

388
00:18:35,911 --> 00:18:38,241
Can you rap for us?

389
00:18:38,241 --> 00:18:39,551
I survived.

390
00:18:39,551 --> 00:18:41,271
I survived with 18 votes.

391
00:18:41,271 --> 00:18:43,831
You scared me. I thought it was him.

392
00:18:43,831 --> 00:18:45,891
I tried it for fun.

393
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:48,251
I hope I can stay in the arena.

394
00:18:48,251 --> 00:18:50,061
I'll stay with you until the end.

395
00:18:50,061 --> 00:18:51,701
Long live, Go Hyeon Guk.

396
00:18:51,701 --> 00:18:53,321
Peace out.

397
00:18:53,321 --> 00:18:54,671
[Keun Suk finishes it off]

398
00:18:54,671 --> 00:18:56,701
[The elite director made a strong impression]

399
00:18:57,101 --> 00:18:59,351
[And more elite directors]

400
00:18:59,351 --> 00:19:02,461
You have a very impressive resume.

401
00:19:02,461 --> 00:19:05,251
You graduated from Ehwa Womans
University early as a valedictorian.

402
00:19:05,251 --> 00:19:08,161
You graduated from KAIST as a valedictorian.

403
00:19:08,161 --> 00:19:11,821
And you got a PhD in Cultural Content
Studies at Hanyang University.

404
00:19:11,821 --> 00:19:13,271
You're a lecturer at Seoul National University

405
00:19:13,271 --> 00:19:16,901
and an adjunct professor at
Dongduk Women's University.

406
00:19:16,901 --> 00:19:18,601
Wow.

407
00:19:18,601 --> 00:19:20,731
I feel so insecure.

408
00:19:20,731 --> 00:19:23,041
Your web drama, "Office Watch"

409
00:19:23,041 --> 00:19:26,271
had Byeon Woo Seok,
Kim Young Dae, and Kang Hoon.

410
00:19:26,271 --> 00:19:28,271
- Wow.
- What a cast.

411
00:19:28,271 --> 00:19:30,311
Those are big names.

412
00:19:30,311 --> 00:19:35,781
People jokingly ask if I know

413
00:19:35,781 --> 00:19:38,701
how to boost male actors.

414
00:19:38,701 --> 00:19:41,551
[Elite Director Lee Soo Ji, male star maker]

415
00:19:41,551 --> 00:19:46,501
Hello, I've directed two short
dramas outside of Korea.

416
00:19:46,501 --> 00:19:48,451
Your resume is so impressive.

417
00:19:48,451 --> 00:19:51,691
I directed "Medical Genius"

418
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:53,311
and "Beyond the Law."

419
00:19:53,311 --> 00:19:55,841
"Medical Genius" got about 20 million views.

420
00:19:55,841 --> 00:19:58,241
[Currently 36 million views]

421
00:19:58,241 --> 00:20:00,181
It was a top show of the week.

422
00:20:00,181 --> 00:20:02,861
[His talent was recognized internationally]

423
00:20:02,861 --> 00:20:05,451
I shoot music videos and commercials.

424
00:20:05,451 --> 00:20:09,081
I'm more known as Cocky.

425
00:20:09,081 --> 00:20:14,341
[Director Cocky's trendy and stylish visuals]

426
00:20:14,341 --> 00:20:16,271
He's a bit different from us.

427
00:20:16,271 --> 00:20:18,861
We got another impressive person.

428
00:20:18,861 --> 00:20:22,211
[What kind of short dramas did
these intimidating directors make?]

429
00:20:22,791 --> 00:20:26,211
Director Lee Soo Ji's "Half Moon Town."

430
00:20:26,211 --> 00:20:30,021
This was the only way to pay off the family debt.

431
00:20:30,021 --> 00:20:32,481
It was to become a criminal.

432
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,271
If I send you a video right now,

433
00:20:34,271 --> 00:20:36,241
can you just delete the YouTube portion?

434
00:20:36,241 --> 00:20:37,661
The fee is a million won.

435
00:20:37,661 --> 00:20:40,151
- Pardon?
- Why would you take off 500 won?

436
00:20:40,151 --> 00:20:42,381
I'm no longer Ms. Nice.

437
00:20:42,381 --> 00:20:43,491
It's too late for that.

438
00:20:43,491 --> 00:20:45,021
Who actually are you?

439
00:20:45,021 --> 00:20:48,161
I told you. I'm a creditor to you
and a criminal to the outside world.

440
00:20:48,161 --> 00:20:49,841
[The stop count is going up]

441
00:20:51,321 --> 00:20:54,321
[You can watch the full versions on Lehzin Snack]

442
00:20:54,731 --> 00:20:57,551
Wow, that was a close one.

443
00:20:57,551 --> 00:20:59,961
Surviving is meaningless with that score.

444
00:20:59,961 --> 00:21:01,811
She's a professor.

445
00:21:01,811 --> 00:21:04,561
I had high hopes hearing all that.

446
00:21:04,561 --> 00:21:06,481
It was too daring.

447
00:21:06,481 --> 00:21:08,481
I'm not really sure.

448
00:21:08,481 --> 00:21:10,031
Why did I not enjoy this?

449
00:21:10,031 --> 00:21:13,131
[She hasn't mastered the world
of short dramas yet]

450
00:21:13,131 --> 00:21:15,671
[How about Director
Yun Hyeong Shik's short drama?]

451
00:21:15,671 --> 00:21:18,241
Hello, I'm idol trainee Kang Shi Yun.

452
00:21:18,241 --> 00:21:21,031
I luckily got a part-time job
at a cafe near the studio.

453
00:21:21,031 --> 00:21:22,401
I need your support.

454
00:21:22,401 --> 00:21:23,811
You're a hater if you don't support me.

455
00:21:23,811 --> 00:21:26,071
[When will we get a hook?]

456
00:21:26,071 --> 00:21:27,991
[Nervous...]

457
00:21:27,991 --> 00:21:29,721
I'll be seeing you soon.

458
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:31,231
Please...

459
00:21:32,231 --> 00:21:34,031
make the right decision.

460
00:21:34,031 --> 00:21:35,801
There wasn't much.

461
00:21:35,801 --> 00:21:36,951
There wasn't much.

462
00:21:36,951 --> 00:21:38,971
I was expecting something to happen.

463
00:21:38,971 --> 00:21:41,551
I guess I was expecting more, too.

464
00:21:41,551 --> 00:21:44,221
[Unexpected critiques and stop count]

465
00:21:44,221 --> 00:21:48,331
[Mid-point ranking of the potential
survivors: 1st to 8th place]

466
00:21:48,331 --> 00:21:52,081
[10th to 20th place]

467
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,491
Clap, clap, clap.

468
00:21:54,491 --> 00:21:56,691
"Clap, clap, clap"?

469
00:21:56,691 --> 00:21:58,741
"Clap, clap, clap"?

470
00:21:58,741 --> 00:22:01,071
[Do we have a comedian?]

471
00:22:01,071 --> 00:22:03,491
- He was in "Gag Concert."
- Really?

472
00:22:03,491 --> 00:22:06,471
I'm his friend, but I love his videos.

473
00:22:06,471 --> 00:22:08,231
Nice to meet you.

474
00:22:09,071 --> 00:22:15,031
Hello, I currently have 908,762 subscribers.

475
00:22:15,031 --> 00:22:17,621
I've been posting a lot of shorts.

476
00:22:17,621 --> 00:22:20,301
[Many videos and unbelievable views]

477
00:22:20,961 --> 00:22:23,981
[His main focus is creating AI shorts]

478
00:22:24,441 --> 00:22:27,491
[His studio is full of laughter]

479
00:22:28,121 --> 00:22:33,841
["When Words Come True"]

480
00:22:33,841 --> 00:22:36,381
Due to bomdong* supply shortage...
(Spring cabbage)

481
00:22:36,381 --> 00:22:40,201
What's this? You have a secret stash of bomdong?

482
00:22:40,201 --> 00:22:41,671
["2026 Bomdong Bibimbap Incident"]

483
00:22:41,671 --> 00:22:43,891
This is Jamsilbon-dong!

484
00:22:43,891 --> 00:22:46,371
It's not bomdong!

485
00:22:46,371 --> 00:22:49,901
I'm Cho Chung Hyeon, a former comedian. Hello!

486
00:22:49,901 --> 00:22:55,661
Your nickname is "900,000 AI Trainer."

487
00:22:55,661 --> 00:22:58,791
Do you have a unique way of training AI?

488
00:22:58,791 --> 00:23:02,131
It doesn't listen when you're nice to it.

489
00:23:02,131 --> 00:23:06,191
I asked for five prompts,
but it only created three.

490
00:23:06,191 --> 00:23:10,061
What do you do when AI doesn't listen to you?

491
00:23:10,061 --> 00:23:11,891
I swear sometimes.

492
00:23:11,891 --> 00:23:14,071
"Create at least 10 based on my prompt.

493
00:23:14,071 --> 00:23:16,111
With no exception. No exception. No exception."

494
00:23:16,111 --> 00:23:17,841
I drilled that into it a bit.

495
00:23:17,841 --> 00:23:20,401
It was better after I yelled at it a bit.

496
00:23:20,401 --> 00:23:22,831
Give me an idea for Director's Arena.

497
00:23:22,831 --> 00:23:24,921
Let's try something unique, then.

498
00:23:24,921 --> 00:23:26,311
For example...

499
00:23:26,311 --> 00:23:28,801
A short drama has to be fun.

500
00:23:28,801 --> 00:23:29,831
Give me something fun.

501
00:23:29,831 --> 00:23:32,411
An unexpected and funny mission was given.

502
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:34,301
What's the unexpected mission?

503
00:23:34,301 --> 00:23:37,481
You always give random answers to my questions.

504
00:23:37,481 --> 00:23:39,051
The balloon flies up...

505
00:23:39,051 --> 00:23:40,741
You fly on a balloon?

506
00:23:40,741 --> 00:23:43,661
You need millions of balloons, then.

507
00:23:43,661 --> 00:23:45,441
The production crew will love that, huh?

508
00:23:45,441 --> 00:23:46,671
Be realistic!

509
00:23:46,671 --> 00:23:47,771
[Reached peak anger]

510
00:23:47,771 --> 00:23:49,971
[Did he successfully finish his teaser?]

511
00:23:49,971 --> 00:23:53,461
"Dwirector's Arena."
I'm curious about this drama.

512
00:23:53,461 --> 00:23:56,311
I didn't plagiarize, by the way.

513
00:23:56,311 --> 00:23:58,811
It's nothing like Director's Arena.

514
00:23:58,811 --> 00:24:00,841
It's "Dwirector's Arena."

515
00:24:00,841 --> 00:24:03,461
The difference is that the prize
money is 10 billion won.

516
00:24:03,461 --> 00:24:05,841
[10-billion-won prize]

517
00:24:05,841 --> 00:24:08,281
- I want to go on that show.
- I love it.

518
00:24:08,281 --> 00:24:10,051
- 10 billion?
- 10 billion.

519
00:24:10,051 --> 00:24:12,821
You won't only see one person's work.

520
00:24:12,821 --> 00:24:16,191
There will be 15, 20, or 100 directors.

521
00:24:16,191 --> 00:24:18,231
You'll see all of their work.

522
00:24:18,231 --> 00:24:20,271
It will be randomized. We'll just choose one.

523
00:24:20,271 --> 00:24:21,791
This will be so fun.

524
00:24:21,791 --> 00:24:23,461
I'm a huge fan.

525
00:24:23,461 --> 00:24:25,221
I'm dying to see it. I can't wait.

526
00:24:25,221 --> 00:24:27,631
- Can we watch it right now?
- For sure.

527
00:24:27,631 --> 00:24:29,431
"For sure"?

528
00:24:29,431 --> 00:24:31,281
Is he an event host?

529
00:24:31,281 --> 00:24:33,421
[Successfully made an impression]

530
00:24:35,141 --> 00:24:37,561
The first directing competition in Korea.

531
00:24:37,561 --> 00:24:40,191
"Dwirector's Arena."

532
00:24:40,191 --> 00:24:42,511
To win the 10 billion won prize,

533
00:24:42,511 --> 00:24:45,701
directors gathered from all over the world.

534
00:24:47,531 --> 00:24:49,491
- It's so well-made.
- Is this all AI?

535
00:24:49,491 --> 00:24:52,151
It's 100%. He's so good with AI.

536
00:24:53,211 --> 00:24:55,311
This is AI, right?

537
00:24:57,591 --> 00:25:00,091
Contestant Boong Joon Ho.

538
00:25:00,091 --> 00:25:01,731
Is this for real?

539
00:25:01,731 --> 00:25:03,131
He's a contestant?

540
00:25:03,131 --> 00:25:04,741
He's known for "Penis Fish."

541
00:25:04,741 --> 00:25:08,741
The penis fish we eat shows up
as a monster at the Han River.

542
00:25:08,741 --> 00:25:10,851
The idea was sensational at the time.

543
00:25:10,851 --> 00:25:12,711
That's an actual penis fish.

544
00:25:12,711 --> 00:25:14,641
So funny.

545
00:25:14,641 --> 00:25:17,461
[Second round of laughter]

546
00:25:17,461 --> 00:25:19,911
It shows up as a monster at the Han River.

547
00:25:19,911 --> 00:25:22,801
The idea was sensational at the time.

548
00:25:23,921 --> 00:25:25,941
"Gisaeng Dance."

549
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:27,451
[Voting starts]

550
00:25:27,451 --> 00:25:28,571
What's that?

551
00:25:28,571 --> 00:25:31,771
Contestant Park Chan Ok.

552
00:25:31,771 --> 00:25:34,101
Known for "Lady Cut-ties."

553
00:25:34,101 --> 00:25:36,771
[He's making everyone laugh, but he's serious]

554
00:25:36,771 --> 00:25:38,181
Do you know me?

555
00:25:38,181 --> 00:25:40,851
Trending director, Jang Hang Jung.

556
00:25:40,851 --> 00:25:43,251
Known for "The King's Tenant."

557
00:25:43,251 --> 00:25:45,301
You're late on rent again, young man.

558
00:25:45,301 --> 00:25:48,421
How dare you disrespect rent?

559
00:25:50,311 --> 00:25:51,911
Is this all AI?

560
00:25:51,911 --> 00:25:54,171
We're approaching the river!

561
00:25:54,171 --> 00:25:56,961
We're approaching the river!

562
00:25:56,961 --> 00:25:58,601
He's on this show?

563
00:25:58,601 --> 00:26:00,771
Really? Crazy.

564
00:26:00,771 --> 00:26:03,431
Contestant Christopher Very Nolan.

565
00:26:03,431 --> 00:26:06,271
Known for "Internstellar."

566
00:26:07,441 --> 00:26:10,091
- I'll go home!
- No!

567
00:26:11,081 --> 00:26:13,311
Don't go home early!

568
00:26:13,311 --> 00:26:16,211
Interns don't go home early!

569
00:26:20,491 --> 00:26:21,621
No way.

570
00:26:21,621 --> 00:26:26,471
The judge is Korea's legendary
comedian, Cho Chung Hyeon.

571
00:26:26,471 --> 00:26:29,821
"Dwirector's Arena."

572
00:26:29,821 --> 00:26:34,121
[The teaser is making the viewers laugh as well]

573
00:26:34,121 --> 00:26:36,171
[Proud]

574
00:26:36,171 --> 00:26:38,251
[Funny]

575
00:26:38,251 --> 00:26:41,131
I got totally sucked in.

576
00:26:41,131 --> 00:26:46,711
Director Cho Chung Hyeon gets
a chance to survive with 22 stops.

577
00:26:46,711 --> 00:26:50,531
Wow. It was made with AI,

578
00:26:50,531 --> 00:26:53,631
but I found it very interesting.

579
00:26:53,631 --> 00:26:57,131
The teaser was so engaging,

580
00:26:57,131 --> 00:27:00,241
but what if this becomes an actual series?

581
00:27:00,241 --> 00:27:02,081
But right now...

582
00:27:02,081 --> 00:27:03,711
We need 50 episodes.

583
00:27:03,711 --> 00:27:05,621
Would that be possible?

584
00:27:05,621 --> 00:27:08,421
Besides these directors,

585
00:27:08,421 --> 00:27:11,681
there are 50 other contestants.

586
00:27:11,681 --> 00:27:13,441
- Will it keep going this way?
- Yes.

587
00:27:13,441 --> 00:27:16,191
There will be Director Lee Byeong Hon.

588
00:27:16,191 --> 00:27:17,621
Lee Byeong Hon?

589
00:27:17,621 --> 00:27:20,431
His film is called "No More Jobs."

590
00:27:20,431 --> 00:27:22,571
- There's a lot more.
- What did you think, Keun Suk?

591
00:27:22,571 --> 00:27:24,791
My head is still filled with question marks.

592
00:27:24,791 --> 00:27:26,421
Filled with question marks.

593
00:27:26,421 --> 00:27:30,451
I want you to mindlessly
consume it without realizing it.

594
00:27:30,451 --> 00:27:32,361
What is it?

595
00:27:32,361 --> 00:27:34,331
I don't quite get the concept.

596
00:27:34,331 --> 00:27:35,931
The concept?

597
00:27:35,931 --> 00:27:39,451
But this is also a matter of taste.

598
00:27:39,451 --> 00:27:42,011
I think that's what I'm worried about, too.

599
00:27:42,011 --> 00:27:43,351
What happens later?

600
00:27:43,351 --> 00:27:45,541
He says there's more,

601
00:27:45,541 --> 00:27:48,441
but I don't think there is.
It feels a bit repetitive.

602
00:27:48,441 --> 00:27:50,291
Repetitive in a bad way.

603
00:27:50,291 --> 00:27:53,921
We had another AI director earlier.

604
00:27:53,921 --> 00:27:56,021
Yes, what did you think?

605
00:27:56,021 --> 00:27:59,131
Aren't you guys like rivals?

606
00:27:59,131 --> 00:28:03,221
His videos appeared on my feed a lot.

607
00:28:03,221 --> 00:28:06,321
I always enjoy them so much.
It was so nice to meet him here.

608
00:28:06,321 --> 00:28:07,901
The story is important,

609
00:28:07,901 --> 00:28:10,761
but as you said, it's mindless entertainment.

610
00:28:10,761 --> 00:28:15,961
And AI seems suited to that kind of content.

611
00:28:15,961 --> 00:28:18,671
I personally enjoyed it a lot.

612
00:28:18,671 --> 00:28:21,161
Do you want the mic?

613
00:28:21,161 --> 00:28:25,521
I've been sitting next to Director Cho all day.

614
00:28:25,521 --> 00:28:27,621
We got to know each other well.

615
00:28:27,621 --> 00:28:31,921
We agreed to form an alliance
and not vote against each other.

616
00:28:31,921 --> 00:28:35,731
- And?
- But I pressed it because I got antsy.

617
00:28:35,731 --> 00:28:37,131
I'm sorry.

618
00:28:37,131 --> 00:28:38,701
[Shocked]

619
00:28:38,701 --> 00:28:41,521
Because she got antsy? That makes no sense.

620
00:28:41,521 --> 00:28:43,721
I enjoyed it a lot.

621
00:28:43,721 --> 00:28:45,741
I'm sorry.

622
00:28:45,741 --> 00:28:48,261
- What does it matter?
- Sorry.

623
00:28:48,261 --> 00:28:49,971
I think I'll throw up.

624
00:28:49,971 --> 00:28:51,711
This is a short drama.

625
00:28:51,711 --> 00:28:53,121
This should be a short drama.

626
00:28:53,121 --> 00:28:54,711
Seriously. It's so funny.

627
00:28:54,711 --> 00:28:57,721
I appreciate your honesty.

628
00:28:57,721 --> 00:29:01,591
If you didn't vote against each other,
it could've been a dirty deal.

629
00:29:01,591 --> 00:29:03,781
But you pressed stop.

630
00:29:03,781 --> 00:29:05,081
[I'm coming over soon!]

631
00:29:05,081 --> 00:29:07,271
Things got a bit uneasy in the end.

632
00:29:07,271 --> 00:29:10,321
[Cho Chung Hyeon gets a chance
to survive with 22 stops]

633
00:29:10,321 --> 00:29:13,451
Let's meet the next director.

634
00:29:13,451 --> 00:29:15,481
It's "No Humans."

635
00:29:15,481 --> 00:29:17,421
"No Humans."

636
00:29:17,421 --> 00:29:20,041
That's not you, is it?
You aren't the actor, are you?

637
00:29:20,041 --> 00:29:22,041
That's not me.

638
00:29:22,811 --> 00:29:25,831
I'm not that scary looking.

639
00:29:26,921 --> 00:29:28,911
It's finally time.

640
00:29:28,911 --> 00:29:32,451
He's popular among the directors.

641
00:29:32,451 --> 00:29:35,261
- Wow. It's powerful.
- Zombies.

642
00:29:35,261 --> 00:29:37,161
- What could it be?
- Is this a zombie one?

643
00:29:37,161 --> 00:29:39,181
- Interesting.
- Looks like a zombie one, right?

644
00:29:39,181 --> 00:29:40,461
Yes.

645
00:29:40,461 --> 00:29:43,251
Hello, I'm videographer Jeong Joo.

646
00:29:43,251 --> 00:29:45,071
I have 11 years of experience.

647
00:29:45,071 --> 00:29:47,451
Music videos, commercials,

648
00:29:47,451 --> 00:29:50,281
directing, art directing, and producing.

649
00:29:50,281 --> 00:29:55,021
I've worked on about 150 projects.

650
00:29:55,021 --> 00:29:58,951
I'm called a world-class music
video director for many reasons.

651
00:29:58,951 --> 00:30:01,751
One is because I've done
K-pop videos for a long time.

652
00:30:01,751 --> 00:30:05,241
BTS. I've worked with
MeloMance since their debut.

653
00:30:05,241 --> 00:30:08,491
NCT and Stray Kids' debut videos.

654
00:30:08,491 --> 00:30:11,431
I've worked with K-pop artists a lot.

655
00:30:11,431 --> 00:30:13,761
[He's worked as a visual director]

656
00:30:13,761 --> 00:30:17,121
[He's branching out
into the world of short dramas]

657
00:30:17,121 --> 00:30:23,921
[He created a teen occult comedy]

658
00:30:26,131 --> 00:30:29,791
Hello, we're FIFTY FIFTY.

659
00:30:29,791 --> 00:30:33,271
I heard Director Jeong Joo,
who directed the video

660
00:30:33,271 --> 00:30:39,191
where we acted for the first time,
will be in the Director's Arena.

661
00:30:39,191 --> 00:30:41,841
Director Jeong Joo, we cheer for you!

662
00:30:41,841 --> 00:30:44,271
Fighting!

663
00:30:44,271 --> 00:30:47,581
[Jeong Joo, a master videographer
who defies genres]

664
00:30:47,581 --> 00:30:51,401
Have you seen
Director Lee's short drama by chance?

665
00:30:51,401 --> 00:30:52,811
Yes, I have.

666
00:30:52,811 --> 00:30:54,891
What did you think?

667
00:30:54,891 --> 00:30:57,031
I'm...

668
00:30:57,031 --> 00:30:58,521
well...

669
00:30:58,521 --> 00:31:00,281
a fan of "Extreme Job."

670
00:31:00,281 --> 00:31:02,741
[Pretending not to care]

671
00:31:03,961 --> 00:31:06,421
He asked about his short drama.

672
00:31:06,421 --> 00:31:09,121
- Sorry...
- I feel like we already got his answer.

673
00:31:09,121 --> 00:31:11,501
- Gosh.
- How awkward.

674
00:31:11,501 --> 00:31:13,241
I'm glad you liked something.

675
00:31:13,241 --> 00:31:14,621
That's understandable.

676
00:31:14,621 --> 00:31:18,561
He won't be petty and press
the button right away...

677
00:31:18,561 --> 00:31:19,921
You're already pressing it.

678
00:31:19,921 --> 00:31:21,531
Why are you pressing it already?

679
00:31:21,531 --> 00:31:23,551
You have to watch it first.

680
00:31:23,551 --> 00:31:28,181
I really enjoyed "Extreme Job."

681
00:31:28,181 --> 00:31:32,881
I think he's upset. I've always
been a straight shooter.

682
00:31:32,881 --> 00:31:35,001
So sorry.

683
00:31:35,001 --> 00:31:37,471
I'm so curious. What's it about?

684
00:31:37,471 --> 00:31:40,321
It's about a fake zombie show.

685
00:31:40,321 --> 00:31:43,471
The hired thugs lie to the residents

686
00:31:43,471 --> 00:31:49,011
that there's a zombie epidemic
in the redevelopment area.

687
00:31:49,011 --> 00:31:52,701
They release fake zombies.
The locals know they're fake,

688
00:31:52,701 --> 00:31:54,331
but they pretend they don't know.

689
00:31:54,331 --> 00:31:56,801
They keep kidnapping innocent infected people

690
00:31:56,801 --> 00:31:58,881
to kick them out of the neighborhood.

691
00:31:58,881 --> 00:32:00,231
That's unusual.

692
00:32:00,231 --> 00:32:03,871
The description is very interesting.

693
00:32:03,871 --> 00:32:06,061
[It's time to become critical]

694
00:32:06,061 --> 00:32:07,981
[No Humans]

695
00:32:07,981 --> 00:32:10,461
[Jeong Joo's "No Humans"]

696
00:32:11,511 --> 00:32:13,841
There was a fire in the last undeveloped area in

697
00:32:13,841 --> 00:32:15,971
Gangnam, Seoul, this morning.

698
00:32:15,971 --> 00:32:18,661
- This looks good.
- My gosh.

699
00:32:18,661 --> 00:32:20,711
[Jeong Joo's "No Humans"]

700
00:32:20,711 --> 00:32:22,671
- Thankfully, no one was injured...
- So realistic.

701
00:32:22,671 --> 00:32:24,471
but about 80 people lost their homes.

702
00:32:24,471 --> 00:32:26,241
This is Reporter Jang Joo Yeong.

703
00:32:26,241 --> 00:32:30,011
The fire erupted from a house in the back alley.

704
00:32:30,881 --> 00:32:32,831
[Scared me]

705
00:32:32,831 --> 00:32:34,551
[Shaking]

706
00:32:35,391 --> 00:32:37,141
[About 4,000 families are driven out every year]

707
00:32:38,751 --> 00:32:41,341
Wow, what great acting skills.

708
00:32:41,341 --> 00:32:43,361
He could become an actor.

709
00:32:44,271 --> 00:32:46,421
Hyung, he looks excited.

710
00:32:46,421 --> 00:32:50,281
- He wouldn't actually bite them, right?
- I'm sure he's fine.

711
00:32:50,281 --> 00:32:52,711
Didn't you hear the scream just now?

712
00:32:52,711 --> 00:32:54,871
She probably passed out already.

713
00:32:54,871 --> 00:32:57,311
[There are 274 redevelopment areas left in Seoul]

714
00:32:58,421 --> 00:33:00,621
- Spare me.
- Oh, my God!

715
00:33:00,621 --> 00:33:02,751
You spooked me, bastard.

716
00:33:02,751 --> 00:33:04,841
- What happened to the lady?
- Hyungnim...

717
00:33:04,841 --> 00:33:07,121
[The last person standing gets
the best leverage in the negotiation]

718
00:33:07,121 --> 00:33:11,771
[Getting sucked in]

719
00:33:17,091 --> 00:33:19,041
Hey, come on.

720
00:33:19,041 --> 00:33:20,771
You can get up now.

721
00:33:21,591 --> 00:33:23,661
You don't have to do this.

722
00:33:23,661 --> 00:33:25,631
W-What's this?

723
00:33:25,631 --> 00:33:27,601
What are you saying to that zombie?

724
00:33:27,601 --> 00:33:30,371
Ahjumma, go upstairs.

725
00:33:30,371 --> 00:33:31,261
You'll get infected.

726
00:33:31,261 --> 00:33:32,771
[Forceful evacuation is no longer possible]

727
00:33:32,771 --> 00:33:35,481
Hyung, I think he's actually dead.

728
00:33:35,481 --> 00:33:37,251
[Hmm...]

729
00:33:37,621 --> 00:33:39,281
[One vote]

730
00:33:39,281 --> 00:33:42,681
[Even the world-class director is nervous]

731
00:33:46,491 --> 00:33:48,861
[The last option is to convince them
that the world has collapsed]

732
00:33:53,121 --> 00:33:57,501
Ahjumma, how many residents are left here?

733
00:33:57,501 --> 00:33:59,271
[No Humans]

734
00:34:00,701 --> 00:34:03,041
[Gets a chance to survive with 15 stop counts]

735
00:34:03,041 --> 00:34:05,971
- Wow.
- That was so engaging.

736
00:34:05,971 --> 00:34:08,041
[The other directors approve
this zombie thriller]

737
00:34:08,041 --> 00:34:11,101
Since he's made music videos and commercials,

738
00:34:11,101 --> 00:34:13,701
- the cinematography was polished.
- Right.

739
00:34:13,701 --> 00:34:15,481
Of all the teasers we've seen today,

740
00:34:15,481 --> 00:34:20,861
I think this one communicated most effectively.

741
00:34:20,861 --> 00:34:26,281
With just the onscreen text descriptions,

742
00:34:26,281 --> 00:34:31,251
I was able to understand
what was going on clearly.

743
00:34:31,251 --> 00:34:34,241
I found it very engaging.

744
00:34:34,241 --> 00:34:35,511
Thank you.

745
00:34:35,511 --> 00:34:38,341
Director Lee, what did you think?

746
00:34:38,341 --> 00:34:41,121
Well, I liked the BTS music videos.

747
00:34:41,121 --> 00:34:43,301
[Holding a grudge]

748
00:34:43,301 --> 00:34:44,921
That wasn't revenge, was it?

749
00:34:44,921 --> 00:34:46,501
[For what he said earlier?]

750
00:34:46,501 --> 00:34:48,301
Director Lee.

751
00:34:48,301 --> 00:34:51,021
I see what you intended.

752
00:34:51,021 --> 00:34:52,561
It's not a teaser.

753
00:34:52,561 --> 00:34:56,571
I think you took the beginning of the short drama

754
00:34:56,571 --> 00:34:58,091
and showed it to us.

755
00:34:58,091 --> 00:35:00,551
It's like you showed us the first episode.

756
00:35:00,551 --> 00:35:02,521
I think that's what you intended.

757
00:35:02,521 --> 00:35:06,071
I thought, "This could be a teaser, too.

758
00:35:06,071 --> 00:35:09,091
Because it's a short drama."

759
00:35:09,091 --> 00:35:10,761
But I pressed the button.

760
00:35:10,761 --> 00:35:12,691
- You did?
- Seriously.

761
00:35:12,691 --> 00:35:15,851
I must've kept thinking it had to be a teaser.

762
00:35:15,851 --> 00:35:18,221
I pressed it and regretted it a bit.

763
00:35:18,221 --> 00:35:19,871
Thank you.

764
00:35:19,871 --> 00:35:21,061
He's thanking you.

765
00:35:21,061 --> 00:35:23,221
I got the same impression.

766
00:35:23,221 --> 00:35:26,811
It felt like we saw an episode.

767
00:35:26,811 --> 00:35:30,591
He passed out from getting hit by a jokbal.

768
00:35:30,591 --> 00:35:32,611
I think that was the highlight.

769
00:35:32,611 --> 00:35:34,831
But it felt too relaxed afterward.

770
00:35:34,831 --> 00:35:38,661
I voted because I thought
it was a bit weak as a teaser.

771
00:35:38,661 --> 00:35:42,521
- You won't be mad, right?
- I agree. I totally agree.

772
00:35:42,521 --> 00:35:43,981
Hello.

773
00:35:43,981 --> 00:35:46,671
This is Director Kim Dong Ha.

774
00:35:46,671 --> 00:35:47,671
[So nervous]

775
00:35:47,671 --> 00:35:52,581
Hello, I'm a comedy director, Kim Dong Ha.

776
00:35:52,581 --> 00:35:54,941
I started by working on an independent film set.

777
00:35:54,941 --> 00:35:58,391
I've been directing short films since then.

778
00:35:59,361 --> 00:36:01,571
[Kim Dong Ha]

779
00:36:01,571 --> 00:36:04,481
The director of "Stand Up Love."

780
00:36:04,481 --> 00:36:06,611
[Thumbnail with strong colors]

781
00:36:06,611 --> 00:36:09,601
Did I read that wrong just now?

782
00:36:09,601 --> 00:36:10,881
What is it?

783
00:36:10,881 --> 00:36:13,501
- It says "sex."
