- Yes.

1039
00:48:13,521 --> 00:48:15,841
[The teaser was very polarizing]

1040
00:48:15,841 --> 00:48:19,261
[Which director will add to the chaos next?]

1041
00:48:19,261 --> 00:48:20,491
[Huh?]

1042
00:48:20,491 --> 00:48:23,411
[The next contestant is drawing attention]

1043
00:48:23,411 --> 00:48:25,101
Here he is, finally.

1044
00:48:25,101 --> 00:48:26,681
[Chatting]

1045
00:48:26,681 --> 00:48:29,691
[Who's the last contestant of Director's Arena?]

1046
00:48:30,421 --> 00:48:33,251
It was Director Lee Joo Seung.

1047
00:48:33,251 --> 00:48:35,411
It's a very familiar face.

1048
00:48:35,411 --> 00:48:39,111
Yes, I'm actor Lee Joo Seung.

1049
00:48:40,391 --> 00:48:44,151
I directed two short films.

1050
00:48:45,141 --> 00:48:47,641
[Actor Lee Joo Seung joins
a short drama competition]

1051
00:48:47,641 --> 00:48:50,831
Since I've acted for 20 years,

1052
00:48:50,831 --> 00:48:55,021
I'm passionate about directing actors.

1053
00:48:55,021 --> 00:48:58,701
I think my insight is my strength.

1054
00:48:59,531 --> 00:49:03,261
[Many actors have joined the competition]

1055
00:49:03,261 --> 00:49:04,621
[Actor, actor, actor]

1056
00:49:05,221 --> 00:49:09,251
[Transforming from actors to be
chosen to directors who plan!]

1057
00:49:09,251 --> 00:49:11,431
[However!]

1058
00:49:11,921 --> 00:49:16,621
[The world of short drama
has been harsh to them!]

1059
00:49:16,991 --> 00:49:20,201
[One of them got eliminated...]

1060
00:49:20,731 --> 00:49:22,931
[The only actor who received zero stops]

1061
00:49:22,931 --> 00:49:27,411
You survived cleanly, Director Lee Yoo Jin.

1062
00:49:27,411 --> 00:49:30,171
[What result will Lee Joo Seung get?]

1063
00:49:31,281 --> 00:49:34,161
It will either go well or not.

1064
00:49:34,161 --> 00:49:36,631
Even if it doesn't,

1065
00:49:36,631 --> 00:49:39,981
I won't die or anything. It's okay.

1066
00:49:39,981 --> 00:49:44,441
I'm curious why you want to direct short dramas.

1067
00:49:44,441 --> 00:49:46,821
I'm a huge fan of the thriller genre.

1068
00:49:46,821 --> 00:49:53,121
I've thought a lot about how the
genre could work in a short form.

1069
00:49:53,121 --> 00:49:58,821
The existing short dramas contain
many provocative scenarios.

1070
00:49:58,821 --> 00:50:04,391
I'm curious if I could get people
hooked without any of that.

1071
00:50:04,391 --> 00:50:05,571
That's why I'm here.

1072
00:50:05,571 --> 00:50:10,751
You're expecting "Kuekkuku" to cost 6.4 billion.

1073
00:50:10,751 --> 00:50:12,451
My heart fluttered just now.

1074
00:50:12,451 --> 00:50:15,101
A 6.4-billion-won short drama?

1075
00:50:15,101 --> 00:50:18,181
What's the budget you're
considering for "Kuekkuku"?

1076
00:50:19,201 --> 00:50:21,301
I'm thinking about 6.4 billion.

1077
00:50:21,301 --> 00:50:22,661
[About 6.4 billion]

1078
00:50:22,661 --> 00:50:24,691
[A short drama mogul]

1079
00:50:24,691 --> 00:50:28,271
I was joking. It was more like a wish.

1080
00:50:28,271 --> 00:50:32,571
The budget shouldn't be low just
because it's a short drama.

1081
00:50:32,571 --> 00:50:34,831
I was speaking for all the directors here.

1082
00:50:34,831 --> 00:50:36,561
Just saying the number made my heart flutter.

1083
00:50:36,561 --> 00:50:38,551
6.4 billion?

1084
00:50:38,551 --> 00:50:41,921
When I first heard the title,

1085
00:50:41,921 --> 00:50:43,911
I thought it was comedy, to be honest.

1086
00:50:43,911 --> 00:50:45,181
"Kuekkuku"?

1087
00:50:45,181 --> 00:50:47,871
But it looks like it's a thriller.

1088
00:50:47,871 --> 00:50:50,981
What's the meaning of the title?
Is it onomatopoeia?

1089
00:50:50,981 --> 00:50:54,761
It's about overhearing a murder scene.

1090
00:50:54,761 --> 00:50:59,151
When a person dies, puking blood, you go "kuek."

1091
00:50:59,151 --> 00:51:02,551
And when you hear someone
chuckling at the same time,

1092
00:51:02,551 --> 00:51:04,921
it would sound like that.

1093
00:51:04,921 --> 00:51:09,301
Hearing the explanation, it's a gruesome title.

1094
00:51:09,301 --> 00:51:11,571
- It's so creepy.
- Should we check it out?

1095
00:51:11,571 --> 00:51:15,621
The title suggests it will be hyper-realistic.

1096
00:51:15,621 --> 00:51:17,261
Should we watch the teaser?

1097
00:51:17,261 --> 00:51:19,221
Yes, do I not need to explain it?

1098
00:51:19,221 --> 00:51:21,261
Please do. Please do.

1099
00:51:21,261 --> 00:51:23,351
I thought it was enough explanation.

1100
00:51:23,351 --> 00:51:27,251
A best-selling novel author

1101
00:51:27,251 --> 00:51:30,341
isn't able to write his next book
because of sophomore syndrome.

1102
00:51:30,341 --> 00:51:32,941
So, he's ready to give up on everything.

1103
00:51:32,941 --> 00:51:36,561
But he happens to hear a murder
happening next door.

1104
00:51:36,561 --> 00:51:38,701
He needs to report the murder,

1105
00:51:38,701 --> 00:51:41,811
but he gets inspired, and he writes about it.

1106
00:51:41,811 --> 00:51:45,161
He gets hooked on his dopamine rush

1107
00:51:45,161 --> 00:51:47,901
and he gets involved in the crime.

1108
00:51:47,901 --> 00:51:50,141
That's the plot.

1109
00:51:50,141 --> 00:51:53,621
Sounds like my palms will get sweaty.

1110
00:51:53,621 --> 00:51:56,701
I wanted to watch it before
hearing the explanation.

1111
00:51:56,701 --> 00:51:58,631
But I want to watch it more now.

1112
00:51:58,631 --> 00:52:00,051
- I'm curious.
- Okay.

1113
00:52:00,051 --> 00:52:02,831
Let's watch Director Lee Joo Seung's teaser.

1114
00:52:02,831 --> 00:52:05,191
Play the video.

1115
00:52:07,851 --> 00:52:09,691
Because I acted alone,

1116
00:52:09,691 --> 00:52:14,421
it was hard to get 90 seconds out of it.

1117
00:52:14,421 --> 00:52:16,261
I'm curious what they would think.

1118
00:52:16,261 --> 00:52:19,571
I think getting an average score
will still be a success.

1119
00:52:19,571 --> 00:52:21,591
That's what I'm thinking.

1120
00:52:22,151 --> 00:52:24,651
[A thriller master has entered the competition]

1121
00:52:24,651 --> 00:52:27,941
[Lee Joo Seung's "Kuekkuku"]

1122
00:52:34,271 --> 00:52:37,321
[A murderer moved next door to me]

1123
00:52:39,371 --> 00:52:43,031
[And I'm writing about his murders]

1124
00:52:45,981 --> 00:52:48,181
[Already scared]

1125
00:52:48,181 --> 00:52:50,271
[Nervous]

1126
00:52:57,311 --> 00:53:00,671
[Voting starts]

1127
00:53:06,601 --> 00:53:09,611
[She inspires me]

1128
00:53:12,811 --> 00:53:15,491
[Stopping after one stop]

1129
00:53:15,491 --> 00:53:18,241
[Until I finish my novel]

1130
00:53:20,711 --> 00:53:22,821
[She cannot...]

1131
00:53:24,501 --> 00:53:27,011
[The stop count is going up]

1132
00:53:27,011 --> 00:53:29,651
[stop the killing]

1133
00:53:44,301 --> 00:53:46,951
[Peak intensity]

1134
00:53:54,021 --> 00:53:56,471
[Kuekkuku]

1135
00:53:56,471 --> 00:53:59,261
[You can watch the full versions on Lehzin Snack]

1136
00:53:59,261 --> 00:54:02,391
- Wow.
- That was great.

1137
00:54:02,391 --> 00:54:05,461
[Confusing expressions?]

1138
00:54:05,461 --> 00:54:08,111
[What's Director Lee Joo Seung's result?]

1139
00:54:08,111 --> 00:54:10,221
Director Lee Joo Seung...

1140
00:54:10,221 --> 00:54:12,621
[The fate of his thriller is?]

1141
00:54:12,621 --> 00:54:18,491
With 23 stops,

1142
00:54:18,491 --> 00:54:20,631
you get a chance to survive.

1143
00:54:20,631 --> 00:54:24,821
Wow. The number spiked in a certain scene.

1144
00:54:24,821 --> 00:54:27,961
- Which scene? Do you remember?
- In the beginning,

1145
00:54:27,961 --> 00:54:30,281
things went very smoothly.

1146
00:54:30,281 --> 00:54:33,921
After the explanation, we thought
we'd see something more...

1147
00:54:33,921 --> 00:54:38,351
visually impactful. But we didn't. Is that why?

1148
00:54:38,351 --> 00:54:42,681
I think he got more votes than I thought.

1149
00:54:42,681 --> 00:54:44,751
- I...
- Did you dislike it?

1150
00:54:44,751 --> 00:54:46,551
No, no. I didn't push the button.

1151
00:54:46,551 --> 00:54:48,721
You didn't? He didn't. He didn't.

1152
00:54:48,721 --> 00:54:51,361
It got me thinking a lot.

1153
00:54:51,361 --> 00:54:53,161
The strawberries,

1154
00:54:53,161 --> 00:54:55,831
and the flipped-over screen, too.

1155
00:54:55,831 --> 00:54:58,891
I think you carefully designed each scene.

1156
00:54:58,891 --> 00:55:02,811
There are thriller movie tropes

1157
00:55:02,811 --> 00:55:06,961
like the editing, music,
and the actor's expressions.

1158
00:55:06,961 --> 00:55:09,491
But I think you have a unique style.

1159
00:55:09,491 --> 00:55:12,571
I thought I should watch it until the end.

1160
00:55:12,571 --> 00:55:14,121
I enjoyed it.

1161
00:55:14,121 --> 00:55:16,831
To interview our viewers,

1162
00:55:16,831 --> 00:55:20,191
I will pick on someone directly.

1163
00:55:20,191 --> 00:55:22,941
- Get nervous.
- That's good, too.

1164
00:55:22,941 --> 00:55:26,771
Second row. The viewer with a green beanie.

1165
00:55:26,771 --> 00:55:29,971
Why did you have to wear a beanie?

1166
00:55:29,971 --> 00:55:32,051
I pressed the button.

1167
00:55:32,051 --> 00:55:37,701
The reason is that his approach was too literal.

1168
00:55:37,701 --> 00:55:41,351
If it were more atmospheric,

1169
00:55:41,351 --> 00:55:43,621
it would've aroused my curiosity.

1170
00:55:43,621 --> 00:55:45,101
It was scary.

1171
00:55:45,101 --> 00:55:47,021
Did you press the button, Director?

1172
00:55:47,021 --> 00:55:51,291
I pressed the button.

1173
00:55:51,291 --> 00:55:54,441
You created suspense with music in the beginning.

1174
00:55:54,441 --> 00:55:57,091
When the music reached its climax,

1175
00:55:57,091 --> 00:56:00,281
at that moment, I thought I'd see something new.

1176
00:56:00,281 --> 00:56:03,471
Like the murder scene

1177
00:56:03,471 --> 00:56:06,981
or something from behind the wall.

1178
00:56:06,981 --> 00:56:08,421
I was hoping to see that,

1179
00:56:08,421 --> 00:56:11,711
but watching it as a viewer,

1180
00:56:12,691 --> 00:56:14,691
I lost interest.

1181
00:56:15,781 --> 00:56:17,891
[Getting beaten up]

1182
00:56:17,891 --> 00:56:23,841
I didn't care if Lee Joo Seung
directed it or not.

1183
00:56:23,841 --> 00:56:27,291
Did something bad happen to you earlier?

1184
00:56:27,291 --> 00:56:30,041
Do you often post hateful comments?

1185
00:56:30,041 --> 00:56:32,071
Did you receive an unpleasant phone call?

1186
00:56:32,071 --> 00:56:35,271
I have to let it all out
to avoid posting a comment.

1187
00:56:35,271 --> 00:56:38,901
- This criticism could be helpful to you.
- It's good. It's good.

1188
00:56:38,901 --> 00:56:41,131
I enjoyed it.

1189
00:56:41,131 --> 00:56:43,071
You aren't upset, are you?

1190
00:56:43,071 --> 00:56:45,201
I'm very hurt.

1191
00:56:45,201 --> 00:56:46,681
[LOL]

1192
00:56:47,881 --> 00:56:49,681
I think it's something

1193
00:56:49,681 --> 00:56:53,341
I can show in the actual series later.

1194
00:56:53,341 --> 00:56:55,371
I didn't feel hurt or anything.

1195
00:56:55,371 --> 00:56:57,971
[Round 1's judging has ended]

1196
00:56:57,971 --> 00:57:00,161
For the first time, we have zero stops.

1197
00:57:00,161 --> 00:57:01,881
- You've survived.
- You've survived.

1198
00:57:01,881 --> 00:57:03,541
[Due to the ruthless stop votes,]

1199
00:57:03,541 --> 00:57:05,911
[three directors got eliminated in Round 1]

1200
00:57:05,911 --> 00:57:08,481
[Three are safe, and three are
eliminated in Round 1]

1201
00:57:09,631 --> 00:57:11,641
[What will determine the
remaining 27 directors' fate?]

1202
00:57:11,641 --> 00:57:14,811
Who held the viewers' attention the longest?

1203
00:57:14,811 --> 00:57:18,611
That will be the criterion
in determining the ranking.

1204
00:57:18,611 --> 00:57:21,511
Let me announce the final results.

1205
00:57:23,711 --> 00:57:27,481
[The stop ranking can be flipped
by the view duration!]

1206
00:57:27,481 --> 00:57:29,531
[Unpredictable result]

1207
00:57:29,951 --> 00:57:34,141
[Don't relax! But don't give up, either!]

1208
00:57:34,141 --> 00:57:37,681
[Who will be chosen as survivors?]

1209
00:57:38,701 --> 00:57:41,691
[Round 1, the teaser mission
for 33 directors has ended]

1210
00:57:41,691 --> 00:57:45,681
Short drama directing competition,
Director's Arena.

1211
00:57:45,681 --> 00:57:49,051
Round 1: Complete a 90-second teaser.

1212
00:57:49,051 --> 00:57:52,101
I'll announce the final results.

1213
00:57:53,261 --> 00:57:56,941
The number of directors
who are advancing to Round 2

1214
00:57:56,941 --> 00:58:02,171
is 16 in total.

1215
00:58:03,871 --> 00:58:06,901
[Only 16 directors get to advance to Round 2!]

1216
00:58:06,901 --> 00:58:11,761
[Mid-point ranking of the potential
survivors: 1st to 11th place]

1217
00:58:11,761 --> 00:58:17,011
[Mid-point ranking of the potential
survivors: 13th to 27th place]

1218
00:58:17,011 --> 00:58:21,051
I'll announce the three directors who are

1219
00:58:21,051 --> 00:58:26,711
definitely advancing with fewer than seven stops.

1220
00:58:26,711 --> 00:58:29,331
- They're the top ones today.
- I'm jealous.

1221
00:58:29,331 --> 00:58:32,831
Lee Yoo Jin, Han Sang Il,
and Han Soo Ji. Congratulations.

1222
00:58:32,831 --> 00:58:35,121
Please move to the survivors' seats.

1223
00:58:35,121 --> 00:58:39,441
The three of you must've been relaxed.

1224
00:58:39,441 --> 00:58:42,811
[Heading to the survivors' seats]

1225
00:58:42,811 --> 00:58:45,101
[Three out of 16 directors]

1226
00:58:45,101 --> 00:58:48,311
[Looking proud]

1227
00:58:48,311 --> 00:58:52,001
Getting zero stops is truly impressive.

1228
00:58:52,001 --> 00:58:55,281
Only one director received zero stops.

1229
00:58:55,281 --> 00:58:58,191
For the first time, we have zero stops.

1230
00:58:58,191 --> 00:59:03,131
You survived cleanly, Director Lee Yoo Jin.

1231
00:59:04,921 --> 00:59:06,961
I was obviously thrilled.

1232
00:59:06,961 --> 00:59:09,011
I haven't experienced something
like this that often.

1233
00:59:09,011 --> 00:59:16,091
My efforts were rewarded as much as I hoped for.

1234
00:59:16,091 --> 00:59:18,911
In the 2nd place is Director Han Sang Il.

1235
00:59:18,911 --> 00:59:21,591
"My Love Story Only I Don't Know About."

1236
00:59:21,591 --> 00:59:22,841
[The unforgettable doghouse strike]

1237
00:59:22,841 --> 00:59:25,411
[His directing impressed the judges]

1238
00:59:25,411 --> 00:59:29,091
[The B-rated style got everyone excited]

1239
00:59:29,091 --> 00:59:32,621
In 3rd place is Director Han Soo Ji.

1240
00:59:32,621 --> 00:59:34,211
"Snakes and Ladders."

1241
00:59:34,211 --> 00:59:39,011
[The characters are trapped in a game
in this school survival thriller]

1242
00:59:39,721 --> 00:59:42,311
[Director's Arena's first survivor]

1243
00:59:42,311 --> 00:59:44,151
Five people pressed the stop button.

1244
00:59:44,151 --> 00:59:46,301
The viewing duration was 86.31 seconds.

1245
00:59:46,301 --> 00:59:48,041
The two were neck-and-neck.

1246
00:59:48,041 --> 00:59:51,291
The difference is just 0.6 seconds.

1247
00:59:52,191 --> 00:59:59,381
There will be 27 surviving directors in total.

1248
00:59:59,381 --> 01:00:06,761
Only 13 of them get to advance to Round 2.

1249
01:00:06,761 --> 01:00:09,051
There are 13 survivors left.

1250
01:00:09,051 --> 01:00:11,551
[Choi Gwi Hwa got 27 stops]

1251
01:00:12,021 --> 01:00:15,751
[Who will take the remaining 13 seats?]

1252
01:00:15,751 --> 01:00:18,881
I'll announce the survivor for each rank.

1253
01:00:18,881 --> 01:00:23,171
Let's reveal the 4th, 5th, and 6th places.

1254
01:00:25,121 --> 01:00:27,051
I can't watch.

1255
01:00:27,971 --> 01:00:29,831
Please reveal.

1256
01:00:29,831 --> 01:00:32,361
[Park So Rang, 15 stops]

1257
01:00:33,121 --> 01:00:37,371
[Some of them got the same number of stops]

1258
01:00:37,371 --> 01:00:41,081
[Will this end up being the final ranking?]

1259
01:00:42,431 --> 01:00:45,281
Except for the Top 3,

1260
01:00:45,281 --> 01:00:48,051
I think mine was the best.

1261
01:00:48,051 --> 01:00:51,081
I was half worried and half excited.

1262
01:00:51,081 --> 01:00:52,851
[Jeong Joo is in 6th place with 15 stops]

1263
01:00:52,851 --> 01:00:55,181
[Park So Rang is also in 6th place with 15 stops]

1264
01:00:55,181 --> 01:00:57,401
Please reveal.

1265
01:00:59,531 --> 01:01:02,071
[4th place: Seo Jun Gyo /
5th place: Lee Dong Hun]

1266
01:01:02,071 --> 01:01:04,571
[Their ranks switched]

1267
01:01:05,171 --> 01:01:06,871
What? Me?

1268
01:01:07,651 --> 01:01:09,541
I'm in 4th place?

1269
01:01:09,541 --> 01:01:11,931
[From 5th place to 4th place]

1270
01:01:11,931 --> 01:01:15,271
I thought I'd be in 5th place,
but I got 4th place.

1271
01:01:15,271 --> 01:01:17,671
I didn't think it was possible. I was thrilled.

1272
01:01:17,671 --> 01:01:19,581
Director Lee Dong Hun got 10 stops

1273
01:01:19,581 --> 01:01:22,721
at 79.24 seconds. He's in 5th place.

1274
01:01:22,721 --> 01:01:24,241
[From 4th place to 5th place]

1275
01:01:24,241 --> 01:01:25,991
I was disappointed.

1276
01:01:25,991 --> 01:01:27,521
They swapped.

1277
01:01:27,521 --> 01:01:31,951
Because of the stop count and viewing duration.

1278
01:01:31,951 --> 01:01:33,071
It's important.

1279
01:01:33,071 --> 01:01:36,771
Director Lee Dong Hun got 10 stops.

1280
01:01:36,771 --> 01:01:38,941
It's fewer than Director Seo Jun Gyo's.

1281
01:01:38,941 --> 01:01:41,631
But the ranking swapped because
of the viewing duration.

1282
01:01:41,631 --> 01:01:43,711
It's not about the stop count.

1283
01:01:43,711 --> 01:01:47,451
The duration of time you
captured people's attention

1284
01:01:47,451 --> 01:01:51,571
is the deciding factor in the ranking.

1285
01:01:51,571 --> 01:01:56,961
I'm realizing the importance
of viewing duration in short dramas.

1286
01:01:56,961 --> 01:02:00,221
The viewing duration matters
more than the stop count.

1287
01:02:00,221 --> 01:02:02,621
I got 15 stops, too.

1288
01:02:03,431 --> 01:02:06,381
[Director Jeong Joo is in 6th place]

1289
01:02:06,381 --> 01:02:08,421
Next is 7th to 9th place.

1290
01:02:08,421 --> 01:02:11,521
I'll reveal the three survivors at once.

1291
01:02:11,521 --> 01:02:13,551
[15 stops vs. 16 stops]

1292
01:02:13,551 --> 01:02:15,591
[Both got 17 stops]

1293
01:02:15,591 --> 01:02:17,381
Please reveal.

1294
01:02:17,381 --> 01:02:19,621
[Round 1 final results]

1295
01:02:19,621 --> 01:02:22,901
[7th, 8th, and 9th places didn't change]

1296
01:02:22,901 --> 01:02:25,501
In 7th place is Director Park So Rang.

1297
01:02:25,501 --> 01:02:27,311
In 8th place is Director Yang Gyeong Hee.

1298
01:02:27,311 --> 01:02:29,881
In 9th place is Director Jang Yu Jin.

1299
01:02:29,881 --> 01:02:32,451
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

1300
01:02:32,451 --> 01:02:36,121
Do you have a favorite so far?

1301
01:02:36,121 --> 01:02:40,421
I had three favorites, but only one survived.

1302
01:02:40,421 --> 01:02:43,471
- I'm happy as a fan.
- Which is it?

1303
01:02:43,471 --> 01:02:45,901
It's okay because they survived.

1304
01:02:45,901 --> 01:02:48,001
- It's "No Humans."
- "No Humans"?

1305
01:02:48,001 --> 01:02:50,031
Right, "No Humans."

1306
01:02:50,031 --> 01:02:52,031
[It's an honor]

1307
01:02:52,031 --> 01:02:54,191
That's my pick as a viewer.

1308
01:02:54,191 --> 01:02:55,691
I'm jealous.

1309
01:02:55,691 --> 01:02:58,471
You got Do Yeon's shout-out.

1310
01:02:58,471 --> 01:03:03,381
I'll announce 11th to 13th place
without further delay.

1311
01:03:03,381 --> 01:03:05,771
[9th place: 17 stops]

1312
01:03:05,771 --> 01:03:07,301
[11th place: 18 stops]

1313
01:03:07,301 --> 01:03:09,411
[12th place: 19 stops]

1314
01:03:09,411 --> 01:03:11,321
[12th place: 19 stops]

1315
01:03:11,751 --> 01:03:15,471
[Will the rankings stay the same again?]

1316
01:03:16,371 --> 01:03:19,011
Please reveal the ranking.

1317
01:03:19,011 --> 01:03:22,591
[What happened, exactly?]

1318
01:03:22,591 --> 01:03:23,941
Daebak.

1319
01:03:24,861 --> 01:03:28,411
[Why is everyone surprised?]

1320
01:03:30,671 --> 01:03:32,821
[12th place: Lee Joo Seung's "Kuekkuku"]

1321
01:03:32,821 --> 01:03:37,841
[Lee Joo Seung is in 12th place out of nowhere]

1322
01:03:38,531 --> 01:03:40,021
[Oh?]

1323
01:03:40,631 --> 01:03:42,671
Me?

1324
01:03:42,671 --> 01:03:45,551
Congrats, Joo Seung.

1325
01:03:45,551 --> 01:03:48,511
[From 16th place to 12th place]

1326
01:03:48,511 --> 01:03:50,331
I got 23 stops.

1327
01:03:50,331 --> 01:03:54,121
So, I thought I was getting eliminated.

1328
01:03:54,121 --> 01:03:57,991
I thought I was very lucky.

1329
01:03:57,991 --> 01:04:01,011
Director Lee Joo Seung's short drama

1330
01:04:01,011 --> 01:04:03,751
had 23 stops, as you can see.

1331
01:04:03,751 --> 01:04:07,891
- But the viewing duration was...
- People watched it for a long time.

1332
01:04:07,891 --> 01:04:10,521
This is what changes things.

1333
01:04:10,521 --> 01:04:12,171
They pressed it at the end.

1334
01:04:12,171 --> 01:04:14,661
Almost toward the end.

1335
01:04:14,661 --> 01:04:16,641
He moved from hell to heaven.

1336
01:04:16,641 --> 01:04:18,661
- We got three seats left.
- That's right.

1337
01:04:18,661 --> 01:04:23,571
There are only three survivors' seats left.

1338
01:04:23,571 --> 01:04:30,761
Who will end up in those seats?

1339
01:04:30,761 --> 01:04:35,021
Let's start with 14th place.

1340
01:04:38,121 --> 01:04:39,511
[18 stops]

1341
01:04:39,511 --> 01:04:41,021
[22 stops]

1342
01:04:41,021 --> 01:04:42,761
[21 stops / 22 stops]

1343
01:04:42,761 --> 01:04:44,401
[23 stops]

1344
01:04:47,481 --> 01:04:52,541
14th place goes to Director Go Hyeon Guk.

1345
01:04:52,541 --> 01:04:54,851
[11th place to 14th place]

1346
01:04:55,411 --> 01:04:58,011
[Congratulations]

1347
01:04:58,011 --> 01:05:02,211
[A screenwriter needs to make
a provocative short drama to survive]

1348
01:05:02,791 --> 01:05:04,711
[The teaser did spike dopamine]

1349
01:05:04,711 --> 01:05:06,611
I saw your confidence.

1350
01:05:06,611 --> 01:05:08,471
It was actually fun.

1351
01:05:08,471 --> 01:05:11,571
It was worth not pushing the button in the end.

1352
01:05:11,571 --> 01:05:12,921
Thank you.

1353
01:05:12,921 --> 01:05:14,611
[Director Go Hyeon Guk is in 14th place]

1354
01:05:14,611 --> 01:05:19,551
There are only two tickets left to Round 2.

1355
01:05:20,961 --> 01:05:23,821
Director's Arena Round 2.

1356
01:05:23,821 --> 01:05:30,781
Reveal the 15th-place director who is advancing.

1357
01:05:30,781 --> 01:05:32,911
[Who's the 15th survivor?]

1358
01:05:34,521 --> 01:05:37,721
[15th place: Oh Hae On's team]

1359
01:05:38,741 --> 01:05:40,541
[Huh?]

1360
01:05:42,551 --> 01:05:45,531
[Dad Cha Tae Hyun is happy
like it's his own work]

1361
01:05:46,131 --> 01:05:48,751
She's crying. Oh, no...

1362
01:05:48,751 --> 01:05:50,651
Of course, she's crying.

1363
01:05:50,651 --> 01:05:52,391
She's the youngest one.

1364
01:05:52,391 --> 01:05:55,261
Good job. You did such a good job.

1365
01:05:56,351 --> 01:05:58,801
I was waiting without expectation.

1366
01:05:58,801 --> 01:06:03,791
But I suddenly saw my name, so I started crying.

1367
01:06:03,791 --> 01:06:07,391
[The other 17-year-olds are also crying]

1368
01:06:07,391 --> 01:06:09,261
Beom Gyu, how many votes did you get?

1369
01:06:09,261 --> 01:06:11,251
I got 23 votes.

1370
01:06:11,251 --> 01:06:12,851
What? What?

1371
01:06:12,851 --> 01:06:14,511
You still don't know, then.

1372
01:06:14,511 --> 01:06:18,211
Right. Joo Seung survived with 23 votes, too.

1373
01:06:18,211 --> 01:06:19,701
[Round 1 final results]

1374
01:06:19,701 --> 01:06:21,881
[12th place: Lee Joo Seung]

1375
01:06:21,881 --> 01:06:25,581
There's just one seat left.

1376
01:06:25,581 --> 01:06:30,621
Which director will get the
final ticket for survival?

1377
01:06:30,621 --> 01:06:36,081
Director's Arena, Round 1's final survivor.

1378
01:06:36,081 --> 01:06:37,841
Who will it be?

1379
01:06:39,151 --> 01:06:40,891
[What does he have to say?]

1380
01:06:40,891 --> 01:06:43,261
We'll be back after the commercial break.

1381
01:06:43,261 --> 01:06:44,441
[Gosh, Ahjussi]

1382
01:06:44,441 --> 01:06:46,511
[Hehe]

1383
01:06:46,511 --> 01:06:48,461
- Do we have commercials?
- Don't we?

1384
01:06:48,461 --> 01:06:50,721
Why don't we make them, too?

1385
01:06:50,721 --> 01:06:54,181
We can make them easily.

1386
01:06:54,181 --> 01:06:55,921
We can't delay any longer.

1387
01:06:55,921 --> 01:06:59,981
Director's Arena, Round 1's final survivor.

1388
01:07:02,241 --> 01:07:06,191
[Smartphone director, Director Eun Jong Hun]

1389
01:07:06,191 --> 01:07:10,551
[Occult goddess, Director Ahn Mi Na]

1390
01:07:10,551 --> 01:07:15,001
[900,000 AI trainer, Director Cho Chung Hyeon]

1391
01:07:15,631 --> 01:07:20,011
[Aiming for Cha Tae Hyun, Director Lee Beom Gyu]

1392
01:07:20,571 --> 01:07:24,791
[Which one of them will be the last survivor?]

1393
01:07:26,961 --> 01:07:31,751
Director's Arena, Round 1's last survivor...

1394
01:07:31,751 --> 01:07:33,171
will be revealed now.

1395
01:07:33,171 --> 01:07:34,121
[Drum roll]

1396
01:07:34,501 --> 01:07:38,921
[Who's the last survivor?]

1397
01:07:43,211 --> 01:07:46,431
Director Eun Jong Hun.

1398
01:07:46,431 --> 01:07:48,411
[I made it...]

1399
01:07:48,411 --> 01:07:49,401
Wow, daebak.

1400
01:07:49,401 --> 01:07:53,211
You're advancing to Round 2 in 16th place.

1401
01:07:53,211 --> 01:07:56,121
Congratulations.
Please go to the survivor's seat.

1402
01:07:56,121 --> 01:07:58,091
[Dramatic moment]

1403
01:07:58,091 --> 01:08:00,381
16th place. I was so happy.

1404
01:08:00,381 --> 01:08:01,791
I was just thrilled.

1405
01:08:01,791 --> 01:08:03,461
I felt like I could work harder

1406
01:08:03,461 --> 01:08:07,201
and have more fun in the next mission.

1407
01:08:07,861 --> 01:08:10,181
This is so unfortunate.

1408
01:08:10,181 --> 01:08:13,121
You all worked very hard.

1409
01:08:13,121 --> 01:08:21,501
I believe this opportunity garnered
a lot of attention for you.

1410
01:08:21,501 --> 01:08:24,721
Don't let this stop you from creating.

1411
01:08:24,721 --> 01:08:29,081
I hope you hang in there
so we can enjoy more of your work.

1412
01:08:29,081 --> 01:08:31,751
- Thank you so much for today.
- Thank you.

1413
01:08:31,751 --> 01:08:33,511
Thank you so much.

1414
01:08:33,511 --> 01:08:35,311
Seeing them leaving,

1415
01:08:35,311 --> 01:08:37,801
I remember the teasers we just saw.

1416
01:08:37,801 --> 01:08:40,351
- It breaks my heart.
- Thank you very much.

1417
01:08:40,351 --> 01:08:44,531
I never thought I'd be
on a competition show like this.

1418
01:08:44,531 --> 01:08:46,511
It was a great experience.

1419
01:08:46,511 --> 01:08:51,331
I got to learn a new way and

1420
01:08:51,331 --> 01:08:53,871
new possibilities in film making.

1421
01:08:53,871 --> 01:08:57,911
I'm happy that I learned a lot from this.

1422
01:08:57,911 --> 01:08:59,231
I am definitely disappointed.

1423
01:08:59,231 --> 01:09:03,851
I hope to come back better and different.

1424
01:09:03,851 --> 01:09:06,311
I'll work very hard...

1425
01:09:06,311 --> 01:09:09,861
so I can come back with better work.

1426
01:09:09,861 --> 01:09:15,051
This is the end of the line for Short Track,

1427
01:09:15,051 --> 01:09:18,551
but I hope the other directors create
short dramas that represent Korea

1428
01:09:18,551 --> 01:09:21,531
and create an international hit.

1429
01:09:21,531 --> 01:09:23,981
We cheer for you. Fighting!

1430
01:09:23,981 --> 01:09:26,891
We'll be back for Season 2.

1431
01:09:26,891 --> 01:09:29,881
Short drama directing competition,
Director's Arena.

1432
01:09:29,881 --> 01:09:33,301
We have 16 directors
who are advancing to Round 2.

1433
01:09:33,301 --> 01:09:37,101
I'll reveal the next mission.

1434
01:09:37,101 --> 01:09:40,621
Round 2 mission is...

1435
01:09:40,621 --> 01:09:44,721
- Let's see. What is it?
- What could it be?

1436
01:09:44,721 --> 01:09:48,641
[What's Round 2 mission?]

1437
01:09:48,641 --> 01:09:50,961
What is it?

1438
01:09:50,961 --> 01:09:52,931
Round 2 mission.

1439
01:09:52,931 --> 01:09:54,781
[Round 2 mission]

1440
01:09:54,781 --> 01:09:57,961
Co-direct a webtoon.

1441
01:09:57,961 --> 01:09:59,531
Wow.

1442
01:09:59,531 --> 01:10:01,591
Co-direct?

1443
01:10:01,591 --> 01:10:03,921
[I hate it]

1444
01:10:04,361 --> 01:10:07,181
- I knew it.
- It's co-directing this time.

1445
01:10:07,181 --> 01:10:10,721
- Okay...
- Huh? It's a team battle.

1446
01:10:10,721 --> 01:10:13,501
- So crazy.
- What do we do?

1447
01:10:13,501 --> 01:10:16,841
You'll form a team with another director

1448
01:10:16,841 --> 01:10:23,011
and make a short drama based
on a popular webtoon.

1449
01:10:23,011 --> 01:10:26,431
When you co-direct,

1450
01:10:26,431 --> 01:10:29,891
you could have disagreements.

1451
01:10:29,891 --> 01:10:33,231
A lot of them don't know each other,
but they have to team up.

1452
01:10:33,231 --> 01:10:38,041
It's like the production crew
wants them to fight.

1453
01:10:38,041 --> 01:10:40,441
What do we do?

1454
01:10:40,441 --> 01:10:43,251
I think this is the worst.

1455
01:10:43,251 --> 01:10:45,471
I swore inside.

1456
01:10:45,471 --> 01:10:48,201
That's what directors hate the most.
You know, right?

1457
01:10:48,201 --> 01:10:50,431
There's a famous saying.

1458
01:10:50,431 --> 01:10:52,971
"One bad captain is better than
two great captains."

1459
01:10:52,971 --> 01:10:57,031
Having two brains is the
worst situation in the industry.

1460
01:10:57,031 --> 01:11:01,181
[Will Round 2 mission go over okay?]

1461
01:11:01,181 --> 01:11:03,371
It's suspenseful because it's unpredictable.

1462
01:11:03,371 --> 01:11:06,071
Short drama directing competition.

1463
01:11:06,071 --> 01:11:09,051
- Ready, action!
- Action.

1464
01:11:09,051 --> 01:11:11,251
[From action to romance, for one single shot]

1465
01:11:11,251 --> 01:11:14,041
[The passionate directors' real film sets]

1466
01:11:14,041 --> 01:11:16,471
I've never acted in trunks before.

1467
01:11:16,471 --> 01:11:19,781
[Nothing can stop them from directing]

1468
01:11:19,781 --> 01:11:23,961
[Actors with eye-catching looks are here]

1469
01:11:24,901 --> 01:11:27,351
Hold on. I can't fall for you...

1470
01:11:27,351 --> 01:11:28,941
Don't go!

1471
01:11:28,941 --> 01:11:30,741
[LOL]

1472
01:11:30,741 --> 01:11:32,581
That was the perfect first episode.

1473
01:11:32,581 --> 01:11:34,221
I thought I wanted to work with you.

1474
01:11:34,221 --> 01:11:36,531
There's no criticism. I loved it.

1475
01:11:36,531 --> 01:11:38,161
It wasn't refreshing.

1476
01:11:38,161 --> 01:11:41,271
It's like well-made seaweed soup
without sesame oil.

1477
01:11:41,271 --> 01:11:43,021
There wasn't anything special about it.

1478
01:11:43,021 --> 01:11:47,561
The average viewing duration will
determine the final ranking.

1479
01:11:47,561 --> 01:11:51,171
[The results are full of twists and turns]

1480
01:11:52,081 --> 01:11:54,021
Please, don't press it.

1481
01:11:54,021 --> 01:11:55,831
I might get eliminated.

1482
01:11:55,831 --> 01:11:57,931
This probably can't be beat.

1483
01:11:57,931 --> 01:11:59,531
I can't tell what they're thinking.

1484
01:11:59,531 --> 01:12:01,601
Geez, I'm screwed.
